WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.800
We trust computer algorithms to be perfectly objective problem solvers,

00:00:04.800 --> 00:00:11.520
but this is the New Jim Code, where supposedly neutral math actually inherits human prejudice.

00:00:11.520 --> 00:00:17.360
Take a predictive policing system, analyzing a city map to forecast where future crimes will happen.

00:00:17.360 --> 00:00:23.440
When a system is deliberately built to amplify social hierarchy, that's engineered inequity.

00:00:23.440 --> 00:00:28.880
It happens when algorithms sort people into rigid risk profiles using historical carceral data,

00:00:28.960 --> 00:00:33.600
like flawed gang databases. But how does a system discriminate if its code never

00:00:33.600 --> 00:00:39.680
explicitly mentions race? By relying on blind defaults. Like using an over-policed zip code

00:00:39.680 --> 00:00:45.840
as a proxy for crime. That's default discrimination, inheriting geographical segregation automatically.

00:00:46.480 --> 00:00:51.440
Marginalized groups are also heavily watched by tools that systematically misidentify them,

00:00:51.440 --> 00:00:56.880
like facial recognition. This specific vulnerability of being hypervisible to surveillance

00:00:56.880 --> 00:01:03.600
is known as coded exposure. These dimensions compound. Engineered risk scores, biased zip codes,

00:01:03.600 --> 00:01:08.960
and targeted exposure create a discriminatory feedback loop. The algorithm continuously trains

00:01:08.960 --> 00:01:15.200
itself on the exact skewed data it just generated. This isn't theoretical. In Canada, systems like

00:01:15.200 --> 00:01:21.200
Vancouver Police's Geodash process bulk historical data to direct physical officers on the streets.

00:01:21.200 --> 00:01:25.120
And that predictive city map? It doesn't actually forecast future crime.

00:01:25.120 --> 00:01:27.440
It just automates the biases of the past.
